Diltiazem is a calcium entry blocker, the newest class of drugs to be introduced in the fight against heart disease. Nitrates have been used for more than 50 years, and beta blockers were developed in the 1960s. I think it will mean that more patients will be routinely put on this drug on a long-term basis. Nitrates and beta blockers are the other types commonly prescribed by doctors. Overall, the drug only decreased additional heart attacks 11 percent, which was not statistically significant, Moss said. This is one of the first reports that seems to identify that, he said. 